{"title_page": "Daniel Casey (screenwriter)", "text_new": "{{short description|American screenwriter|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox writer\n| name             = Daniel Casey\n| image            =\n| image_size       =\n| caption          =\n| birth_name       = Daniel Casey\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1981|11|15}}\n| birth_place      = [[Dallas, Texas]]\n| death_date       =\n| death_place      =\n| notableworks     = ''The Death of Michael Smit''h<br>''[[Kin (film)|Kin]]''<br>''[[Fast & Furious 9]]''\n| home_town = [[Detroit, Michigan]]\n| residence = [[Los Angeles, California]]\n| occupation       = [[Screenwriter]]\n| education = [[College for Creative Studies]] ([[Bachelor of Fine Arts|BFA]])<br>[[American Film Institute]] ([[Master of Fine Arts|MFA]])\n| nationality      =\n| alma_mater       =\n| spouse           =\n| yearsactive      = 1999\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Daniel Casey''' (born November 15, 1981) is an [[United States|American]] [[screenwriter]] best known as the writer of the [[2018 in film|2018 film]] ''[[Kin (film)|Kin]]'' <ref name=thecool>{{cite news |last=Horwitz |first=Jane |date=30 August 2018 |title=The cool finale of \u2018Kin\u2019 can\u2019t save the clich\u00e9s that preceded it |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/goingoutguide/movies/the-cool-finale-of-kin-cant-save-the-cliches-that-preceded-it/2018/08/29/8b0e03be-a646-11e8-97ce-cc9042272f07_story.html |work=Washington Post |location=washingtonpost.com |access-date=4 December 2018 }}</ref><ref name=futuristic>{{cite news |last=Kenny |first=Glenn |date=30 August 2018 |title=Review: In \u2018Kin,\u2019 a Futuristic Weapon and Family Troubles |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/08/30/movies/kin-review.html |work=New York Times |location=nytimes.com |access-date=4 December 2018 }}</ref><ref name=verybiggun>{{cite news |last=Coyle |first=Jake |date=29 August 2018 |title=In the Detroit-set 'Kin,' a kid with a very big gun |url=http://www.startribune.com/review-in-the-detroit-set-kin-a-kid-with-a-very-big-gun/492031411/ |work=Associated Press |location=startribune.com |access-date=4 December 2018 }}</ref><ref name=franco>{{cite news |last=McNary |first=Dave |date=30 August 2016 |title= James Franco, Zoe Kravitz, Jack Reynor to Star in Sci-Fi Film \u2018Kin\u2019 |url= https://variety.com/2016/film/news/james-franco-zoe-kravitz-jack-reynor-sci-fi-movie-kin-1201847814// |work=Variety |location=variety.com |access-date=24 January 2019}}</ref> and the latest installment in the [[Fast & Furious|''Fast & Furious'' franchise]], ''[[F9 (film)|F9]]''.<ref name=landskin />\n\n==Early life==\nCasey grew up in [[Royal Oak, Michigan|Royal Oak]], [[Michigan (state)|Michigan]]. He graduated from [[Dondero High School|George A. Dondero High School]] before attending the College for Creative Studies in [[Detroit]], Michigan where he earned his BFA in digital cinema and received his MFA in Film Directing from the American Film Institute, where he was the recipient of the Tom Yoda Scholarship Award.<ref name=crains>{{cite news |date=2009 |title= Twenty In Their 20s |url= https://www.crainsdetroit.com/awards/daniel-casey |work=Crian\u2019s Detroit Business |location=crainsdetroit.com |access-date=25 January 2019}}</ref> Casey with his film ''Poletown'' was selected as one of 13 projects to participate in the annual [[Sundance Institute]]'s June Directors and Screenwriters Labs, held at the [[Sundance Resort]] in [[Utah]].<ref name=sundance>{{cite press release |last=Addicott |first=Brooks |date=30 April 2008 |title= Sundance Institute Announces 13 Projects for the 2008 June Directors and Screenwriters Labs |url= http://www.sundance.org/pdf/press-releases/2008-04-30-screenwriters-directors.pdf |location= sundance.org |publisher= Sundance Institute |agency= Sundance Institute |access-date=2019-01-30}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nCasey has been tapped to replace [[Chris Morgan (writer)|Chris Morgan]] and write the screenplay for latest installment in the Fast & Furious franchise, ''Fast & Furious 9'', due out May 22, 2020.<ref name=landskin>{{cite news |last=Kit |first=Borys |date=14 May 2018 |title='Fast and Furious 9' Lands 'Kin' Writer |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/fast-furious-9-lands-kin-writer-1111726 |work=Hollywood Reporter |location=hollywoodreporter.com |access-date=4 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=fasttaps>{{cite news |last=Kroll |first=Justin |date=14 May 2018 |title= \u2018Fast and Furious 9\u2019 Taps Writer Daniel Casey |url= https://variety.com/2018/film/news/daniel-casey-fast-and-furious-9-1202810251/ |work=Variety |location=variety.com |access-date=24 January 2019}}</ref><ref name=thrillist>{{cite news |last=Stefansky |first=Emma |date=1 August 2019 |title=Everything We Know About 'Fast & Furious 9' |url=https://www.thrillist.com/entertainment/nation/fast-furious-9-release-date-cast-news |work=Thrillist |location=Thrillist.com |access-date=6 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe has been selected to work on [[Sony Pictures|Sony]]'s adaptation of the comic, ''[[Incognito (comics)|Incognito]]'', by [[Ed Brubaker]]. [[Fede \u00c1lvarez (filmmaker)|Fede \u00c1lvarez]] is set to direct.<ref name=Cloverfield>{{cite news |last=Kit |first=Borys |date=11 October 2016 |title=Sony's 'Incognito' Project Enlists Writer Daniel Casey |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/daniel-casey-work-sony-adaptation-937314 |work=Hollywood Reporter |location=hollywoodreporter.com |access-date=22 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe is also attached to another comic book adaptation for the big screen from Brubaker, ''[[Kill or Be Killed (comics)|Kill or Be Killed]]''. It will be directed by [[Chad Stahelski]].<ref name=kill>{{cite news |last=Kit |first=Borys |date=7 December 2017 |title= 'John Wick' Director Tackling Ed Brubaker Comic 'Kill or Be Killed' |url= https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/john-wick-director-tackling-ed-brubaker-comic-kill-be-killed-1066847|work=Hollywood Reporter |location=hollywoodreporter.com |access-date=24 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[J.J. Abrams]]' [[Bad Robot Productions]] is producing Casey's script ''The Heavy'' for [[Paramount Pictures|Paramount]]. The superhero movie is in negotiations with ''[[Overlord (2018 film)|Overlord]]'' director [[Julius Avery]] to direct.<ref name=theheavy>{{cite news |last=Kit |first=Borys |date=3 May 2018 |title= J.J. Abrams, Paramount Plot Superhero Thriller From 'Overlord' Director |url= https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/jj-abrams-paramount-plot-superhero-thriller-overlord-director-1108033 |work=Hollywood Reporter |location=hollywoodreporter.com |access-date=24 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[Blumhouse Productions]] is rumored to be remaking ''[[The Craft (film)|The Craft]]''. Casey is tied to the project with fellow writer [[Zoe Lister-Jones]]. Lister-Jones has also been rumored to direct.<ref name=thecraft>{{cite news |last=Vincent |first=Brittany |date=25 March 2019 |title= BUCKLE UP, WITCHES: THE CRAFT REBOOT HAS REPORTEDLY BEEN GREENLIT |url= http://www.mtv.com/news/3118282/the-craft-reboot-july/ |work=MTV |location=MTV.com |access-date=10 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nCasey currently resides in [[Los Angeles, California]].<ref name=oakland>{{cite news |last=Drake |first=Monica |date=21 December 2010 |title= Ferndale man's film to be shown at Detroit festival |url= https://www.theoaklandpress.com/news/ferndale-man-s-film-to-be-shown-at-detroit-festival/article_063bfa30-5222-5e70-9624-3b842a482ab8.html |work=Oakland Press |location=theoaklandpress.com |access-date=25 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"margin-right: 0;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Director\n! Editor\n! Writer\n! Producer\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2003\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| ''The Passage''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|-\n| 2003\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| ''Secrets of Fenville''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| segment \"Happily Married Vigilantes\"\n|-\n| 2006\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| ''The Death of Michael Smith''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n|\n|-\n| 2008\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| ''Dead Man's Hour''\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n|\n|-\n| 2011\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| ''[[Deadheads (film)|Deadheads]]''\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n|credited with 'Special Thanks'\n|- \n| 2016\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| ''[[10 Cloverfield Lane]]''\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{partial|uncredited}}\n| {{no}}\n|\n|-\n| 2018\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| ''[[Kin (film)|Kin]]''\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n|\n|-\n| 2021\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| ''[[F9 (film)|F9]]''\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"margin-right: 0;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Director\n! Editor\n! Writer\n! Producer\n! Notes\n|-\n\n| 2012\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| ''Dr0ne''\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| 1 episode\n|-\n| 2013\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| ''[[Chosen (TV series)|Chosen]]''\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| 6 episodes\n|-\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Nominated work\n! Result\n|-\n|rowspan=3|2004\n|rowspan=2|[[B-Movie Film Festival]]\n| Best Writer\n|rowspan=3|''The Passage\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Best B-Movie\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|Tambay Film and Video Festival\n|New Filmmaker Award\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2007\n|Slamdance Film Festival\n| Grand Jury Prize for Excellence\n|rowspan=2|''The Death of Michael Smith\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|[[Silver Lake Film Festival]]\n|Best Narrative Feature Award\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|0143403}}\n* {{Vimeo|user=user779368|Daniel Casey}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Casey, Daniel}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1981 births]]\n[[Category:American male screenwriters]]\n\n\n{{US-screenwriter-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American screenwriter|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox writer\n| name             = Daniel Casey\n| image            =\n| image_size       =\n| caption          =\n| birth_name       = Daniel Casey\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1981|11|15}}\n| birth_place      = [[Dallas, Texas]]\n| death_date       =\n| death_place      =\n| notableworks     = ''The Death of Michael Smit''h<br>''[[Kin (film)|Kin]]''<br>''[[Fast & Furious 9]]''\n| home_town = [[Detroit, Michigan]]\n| residence = [[Los Angeles, California]]\n| occupation       = [[Screenwriter]]\n| education = [[College for Creative Studies]] ([[Bachelor of Fine Arts|BFA]])<br>[[American Film Institute]] ([[Master of Fine Arts|MFA]])\n| nationality      =\n| alma_mater       =\n| spouse           =\n| yearsactive      = 1999\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Daniel Casey''' (born November 15, 1981) is an [[United States|American]] [[screenwriter]] best known as the writer of the [[2018 in film|2018 film]] ''[[Kin (film)|Kin]]'' <ref name=thecool>{{cite news |last=Horwitz |first=Jane |date=30 August 2018 |title=The cool finale of \u2018Kin\u2019 can\u2019t save the clich\u00e9s that preceded it |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/goingoutguide/movies/the-cool-finale-of-kin-cant-save-the-cliches-that-preceded-it/2018/08/29/8b0e03be-a646-11e8-97ce-cc9042272f07_story.html |work=Washington Post |location=washingtonpost.com |access-date=4 December 2018 }}</ref><ref name=futuristic>{{cite news |last=Kenny |first=Glenn |date=30 August 2018 |title=Review: In \u2018Kin,\u2019 a Futuristic Weapon and Family Troubles |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/08/30/movies/kin-review.html |work=New York Times |location=nytimes.com |access-date=4 December 2018 }}</ref><ref name=verybiggun>{{cite news |last=Coyle |first=Jake |date=29 August 2018 |title=In the Detroit-set 'Kin,' a kid with a very big gun |url=http://www.startribune.com/review-in-the-detroit-set-kin-a-kid-with-a-very-big-gun/492031411/ |work=Associated Press |location=startribune.com |access-date=4 December 2018 }}</ref><ref name=franco>{{cite news |last=McNary |first=Dave |date=30 August 2016 |title= James Franco, Zoe Kravitz, Jack Reynor to Star in Sci-Fi Film \u2018Kin\u2019 |url= https://variety.com/2016/film/news/james-franco-zoe-kravitz-jack-reynor-sci-fi-movie-kin-1201847814// |work=Variety |location=variety.com |access-date=24 January 2019}}</ref> and the latest installment in the [[Fast & Furious|''Fast & Furious'' franchise]], ''[[F9 (film)|F9]]''.<ref name=landskin />\n\n==Early life==\nCasey grew up in [[Royal Oak, Michigan|Royal Oak]], [[Michigan (state)|Michigan]]. He graduated from [[Dondero High School|George A. Dondero High School]] before attending the College for Creative Studies in [[Detroit]], Michigan where he earned his BFA in digital cinema and received his MFA in Film Directing from the American Film Institute, where he was the recipient of the Tom Yoda Scholarship Award.<ref name=crains>{{cite news |date=2009 |title= Twenty In Their 20s |url= https://www.crainsdetroit.com/awards/daniel-casey |work=Crian\u2019s Detroit Business |location=crainsdetroit.com |access-date=25 January 2019}}</ref> Casey with his film ''Poletown'' was selected as one of 13 projects to participate in the annual [[Sundance Institute]]'s June Directors and Screenwriters Labs, held at the [[Sundance Resort]] in [[Utah]].<ref name=sundance>{{cite press release |last=Addicott |first=Brooks |date=30 April 2008 |title= Sundance Institute Announces 13 Projects for the 2008 June Directors and Screenwriters Labs |url= http://www.sundance.org/pdf/press-releases/2008-04-30-screenwriters-directors.pdf |location= sundance.org |publisher= Sundance Institute |agency= Sundance Institute |access-date=2019-01-30}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nCasey has been tapped to replace [[Chris Morgan (writer)|Chris Morgan]] and write the screenplay for latest installment in the Fast & Furious franchise, ''Fast & Furious 9'', due out May 22, 2020.<ref name=landskin>{{cite news |last=Kit |first=Borys |date=14 May 2018 |title='Fast and Furious 9' Lands 'Kin' Writer |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/fast-furious-9-lands-kin-writer-1111726 |work=Hollywood Reporter |location=hollywoodreporter.com |access-date=4 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=fasttaps>{{cite news |last=Kroll |first=Justin |date=14 May 2018 |title= \u2018Fast and Furious 9\u2019 Taps Writer Daniel Casey |url= https://variety.com/2018/film/news/daniel-casey-fast-and-furious-9-1202810251/ |work=Variety |location=variety.com |access-date=24 January 2019}}</ref><ref name=thrillist>{{cite news |last=Stefansky |first=Emma |date=1 August 2019 |title=Everything We Know About 'Fast & Furious 9' |url=https://www.thrillist.com/entertainment/nation/fast-furious-9-release-date-cast-news |work=Thrillist |location=Thrillist.com |access-date=6 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe has been selected to work on [[Sony Pictures|Sony]]'s adaptation of the comic, ''[[Incognito (comics)|Incognito]]'', by [[Ed Brubaker]]. [[Fede \u00c1lvarez (filmmaker)|Fede \u00c1lvarez]] is set to direct.<ref name=Cloverfield>{{cite news |last=Kit |first=Borys |date=11 October 2016 |title=Sony's 'Incognito' Project Enlists Writer Daniel Casey |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/daniel-casey-work-sony-adaptation-937314 |work=Hollywood Reporter |location=hollywoodreporter.com |access-date=22 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe is also attached to another comic book adaptation for the big screen from Brubaker, ''[[Kill or Be Killed (comics)|Kill or Be Killed]]''. It will be directed by [[Chad Stahelski]].<ref name=kill>{{cite news |last=Kit |first=Borys |date=7 December 2017 |title= 'John Wick' Director Tackling Ed Brubaker Comic 'Kill or Be Killed' |url= https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/john-wick-director-tackling-ed-brubaker-comic-kill-be-killed-1066847|work=Hollywood Reporter |location=hollywoodreporter.com |access-date=24 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[J.J. Abrams]]' [[Bad Robot Productions]] is producing Casey's script ''The Heavy'' for [[Paramount Pictures|Paramount]]. The superhero movie is in negotiations with ''[[Overlord (2018 film)|Overlord]]'' director [[Julius Avery]] to direct.<ref name=theheavy>{{cite news |last=Kit |first=Borys |date=3 May 2018 |title= J.J. Abrams, Paramount Plot Superhero Thriller From 'Overlord' Director |url= https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/jj-abrams-paramount-plot-superhero-thriller-overlord-director-1108033 |work=Hollywood Reporter |location=hollywoodreporter.com |access-date=24 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[Blumhouse Productions]] is rumored to be remaking ''[[The Craft (film)|The Craft]]''. Casey is tied to the project with fellow writer [[Zoe Lister-Jones]]. Lister-Jones has also been rumored to direct.<ref name=thecraft>{{cite news |last=Vincent |first=Brittany |date=25 March 2019 |title= BUCKLE UP, WITCHES: THE CRAFT REBOOT HAS REPORTEDLY BEEN GREENLIT |url= http://www.mtv.com/news/3118282/the-craft-reboot-july/ |work=MTV |location=MTV.com |access-date=10 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nCasey currently resides in [[Los Angeles, California]].<ref name=oakland>{{cite news |last=Drake |first=Monica |date=21 December 2010 |title= Ferndale man's film to be shown at Detroit festival |url= https://www.theoaklandpress.com/news/ferndale-man-s-film-to-be-shown-at-detroit-festival/article_063bfa30-5222-5e70-9624-3b842a482ab8.html |work=Oakland Press |location=theoaklandpress.com |access-date=25 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"margin-right: 0;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Director\n! Editor\n! Writer\n! Producer\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2003\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| ''The Passage''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|-\n| 2003\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| ''Secrets of Fenville''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}